section.section:
The recycled content percentage requirement is:
12% for 1992;
12% for 1993;
20% for 1994, 1995, 1996, 1997, 1998, and 1999;
25% for 2000;
30% for 2001 and 2002;
35% for 2003 and 2004; and
40% for 2005 and all subsequent reporting periods.

The Fund shall consist of:
The newsprint recycling incentive fee;
The telephone directory recycling incentive fee collected under § 9-1709 of this subtitle;
The covered electronic device manufacturer registration fee collected under § 9-1728 of this subtitle;
All fines and penalties collected under this subtitle;
Money appropriated in the State budget to the Fund; and
Any other money from any other source accepted for the benefit of the Fund.

In accordance with the State budget, the Fund shall be used only:
To provide grants to the counties to be used by the counties to develop and implement local recycling plans;
To provide grants to counties that have addressed methods for the separate collection and recycling of covered electronic devices in accordance with § 9-1703(c)(1) of this subtitle;
To provide grants to municipalities to be used by the municipalities to implement local covered electronic device recycling programs; and
To carry out the purposes of the land management administration.

The Newsprint Recycling Board is composed of 9 members appointed by the Governor as follows:
2 shall be representatives of newspaper publishers appointed from a list of at least 5 names submitted by the Maryland Delaware District of Columbia Press Association;
1 shall be a representative of the Northeast Waste Disposal Authority;
1 shall be a representative of the Maryland Environmental Service;
1 shall be a representative of local governments;
1 shall be a representative of the newspaper recycling manufacturing industry;
1 shall be a representative of an industry, other than an industry that uses old newspapers; and
2 shall be representatives of environmental groups with some expertise in recycling.

The Newsprint Recycling Board shall:
Review the reports filed under subsection (e) of this section;
Analyze the availability and utilization of newsprint containing recycled material;
Comment on the appropriateness of the recycled content percentage requirements, including whether the requirements encourage manufacturers of virgin newsprint to convert to recycling;
Comment on the need for continuation of the provisions of this section and the impact the provisions of this section have on users of old newspapers for purposes other than producing newsprint;
Work with municipalities and other collectors of old newspapers to develop a reliable system to provide a stable and quality supply of old newspapers for recycling;
Work to encourage the location of production facilities in the region to ensure an increase in the supply of recycled newsprint; and
Work to encourage the reuse of old newspapers.
